 The gang broke into the store from both the front and the back, clearing out display cabinets and bombing the safe.
Outside heavily armed spotter crews covered both entrances to Dolerite Crescent. The spotter crews opened fire on security companies with AK47’s, and R1 and R5 assault rifles.
More than 150 rounds were fired but luckily no one was injured. At least five vehicles were used for the heist. Video footage clearly shows how the robbers opened fire on security vehicles as they approached the store. Read the full report in today’s Middelburg Observer.       Parents frustrated by a lack of space in Middelburg schools Traffic officers to appear in court for corruption #TrafficAlert: Two dead in Kranspoort accidents VIDEO: Two perish after truck jack-knifes • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za